Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "popijemo" in different forms and positions:

1. Danas *popijemo* kafu zajedno. (Today we will drink coffee together.)
2. Juče smo *popili* sok od pomorandže. (Yesterday we drank orange juice.)
3. Ako *popiješ* previše alkohola, osećaćeš se loše sutradan. (If you drink too much alcohol, you will feel bad the next day.)
4. Kada budemo u kafiću, hajde da *popijemo* nešto osvežavajuće. (When we're at the cafe, let's drink something refreshing.)
5. Jutros sam *popio* čaj umesto kafe. (This morning I drank tea instead of coffee.)
6. Da li želiš da *popiješ* čašu vode pre ručka? (Do you want to drink a glass of water before lunch?)
7. Uvek se dobro *popiti* pre spavanja. (It's always good to have a drink before going to bed.)

Note: The word "popijemo" is conjugated in different forms depending on the tense and person, as shown in the examples above. The word means "to drink (something)" in English. The asterisk (*) is used to highlight the word "popijemo" in each sentence.